history.content:
I originally planned to take CS 61C and another R1B at the same time. Recently I dropped the R1B and wanted to take another six-week course which has a time conflict with the 61C discussion and lab I enrolled in. I do know that CS courses during summer disallow concurrent enrollment, but the case is that the lecture time is not in conflict, and I can choose to go to different discussion and lab (actually I'm attending a different discussion right now, and I'm sure there are empty seats in the ones I will attend) so that everything works fine (also consider the flexible policy of letting students attend different lab/discussion in many CS courses). Now the Calcentral is preventing me from enrolling into a second course due to this conflict issue, and I wonder who should I contact with in order to resolve this issue?

A lot of thanks!
history.subject: Time conflict between 61C and another six-week course
